#. <section class="sutta" id="mn52"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn52:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 52"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 52"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn52:0.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhakanāgarasutta"
msgstr "The Man From the City of Aṭṭhaka"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. VAR: beluvagāmake → veḷuvagāmake (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn52:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando vesāliyaṃ viharati beluvagāmake."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Vesālī in the little village "
"of Beluva."

msgctxt "mn52:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro pāṭaliputtaṃ anuppatto "
"hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the householder Dasama from the city of Aṭṭhaka had arrived "
"at Pāṭaliputta on some business."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro yena kukkuṭārāmo yena aññataro "
"bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro taṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"He went to the Chicken Monastery, approached a certain mendicant, bowed, sat "
"down to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn52:2.2"
msgid "“kahaṃ nu kho, bhante, āyasmā ānando etarahi viharati?"
msgstr "“Sir, where is Venerable Ānanda now staying?"

msgctxt "mn52:2.3"
msgid "Dassanakāmā hi mayaṃ taṃ āyasmantaṃ ānandan”ti."
msgstr "For I want to see him.”"

msgctxt "mn52:2.4"
msgid "“Eso, gahapati, āyasmā ānando vesāliyaṃ viharati beluvagāmake”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Householder, Venerable Ānanda is staying near Vesālī in the little village "
"of Beluva.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro pāṭaliputte taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā "
"yena vesālī yena beluvagāmako yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho "
"dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Dasama, having concluded his business there, went to "
"the little village of Beluva in Vesālī to see Ānanda. He bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to Ānanda:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "mn52:3.2"
msgid ""
"“atthi nu kho, bhante ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā "
"sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino "
"pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā "
"parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, Ānanda, is there one thing that has been rightly explained by the "
"Blessed One—who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha—"
"practicing which a diligent, keen, and resolute mendicant’s mind is freed, "
"their defilements are ended, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.350"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, gahapati, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"ekadhammo akkhāto, yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa "
"viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ "
"gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti."
msgstr "“There is, householder.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:3.4"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā "
"sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto, yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino "
"pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā "
"parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti?"
msgstr "“And what is that one thing?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, gahapati, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Householder, it’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, "
"secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first "
"absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing "
"the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn52:4.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Then they reflect:"

msgctxt "mn52:4.3"
msgid "‘idampi kho paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ."
msgstr "‘Even this first absorption is produced by choices and intentions.’"

msgctxt "mn52:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is "
"impermanent and liable to cessation.’"

msgctxt "mn52:4.5"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti."
msgstr "Abiding in that they attain the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn52:4.6"
msgid ""
"No ce āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti, teneva dhammarāgena tāya dhammanandiyā "
"pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha "
"parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, with the ending of the five "
"lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously, because of their passion and "
"love for that meditation. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to "
"return from that world."

msgctxt "mn52:4.7"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, gahapati, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"ekadhammo akkhāto, yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa "
"viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ "
"gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"This is one thing that has been rightly explained by the Blessed One—who "
"knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha—practicing "
"which a diligent, keen, and resolute mendicant’s mind is freed, their "
"defilements are ended, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.351"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn52:5.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:5.3"
msgid "‘idampi kho dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:5.4"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn52:6.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:6.3"
msgid "‘idampi kho tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:6.4"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption …"

msgctxt "mn52:7.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:7.3"
msgid "‘idampi kho catutthaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:7.4"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: catutthaṃ → catutthiṃ (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: abyābajjhena → abyāpajjhena (bj, s2, s3) | abyāpajjena (s1, mr)
msgctxt "mn52:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā "
"viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho "
"tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā "
"vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of love to one "
"direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the "
"same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart "
"full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of "
"enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "mn52:8.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Then they reflect:"

msgctxt "mn52:8.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho mettācetovimutti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā."
msgstr ""
"‘Even this heart’s release by love is produced by choices and intentions.’"

msgctxt "mn52:8.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is "
"impermanent and liable to cessation.’ …"

msgctxt "mn52:8.5"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:8.6"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.352"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:10.1"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …"
msgstr "rejoicing …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:11.1"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr "equanimity …"

msgctxt "mn52:11.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:11.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho upekkhācetovimutti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:11.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:11.5"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:11.6"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (6–8.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:12.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā "
"paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, householder, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of "
"form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on "
"perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains "
"in the dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "mn52:12.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Then they reflect:"

msgctxt "mn52:12.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpatti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā."
msgstr ""
"‘Even this attainment of the dimension of infinite space is produced by "
"choices and intentions.’"

msgctxt "mn52:12.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is "
"impermanent and liable to cessation.’ …"

msgctxt "mn52:12.5"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:12.6"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:13.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘"
"anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite consciousness. …"

msgctxt "mn52:13.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:13.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpatti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:13.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:13.5"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn52:13.6"
msgid "anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘"
"natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in "
"the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "mn52:14.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Then they reflect:"

msgctxt "mn52:14.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpatti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā."
msgstr ""
"‘Even this attainment of the dimension of nothingness is produced by choices "
"and intentions.’"

msgctxt "mn52:14.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is "
"impermanent and liable to cessation.’"

msgctxt "mn52:14.5"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti."
msgstr "Abiding in that they attain the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn52:14.6"
msgid ""
"No ce āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti, teneva dhammarāgena tāya dhammanandiyā "
"pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha "
"parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, with the ending of the five "
"lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously because of their passion and love "
"for that meditation. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to "
"return from that world."

msgctxt "mn52:14.7"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, gahapati, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"ekadhammo akkhāto yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa "
"viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ "
"gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti. (11)"
msgstr ""
"This too is one thing that has been rightly explained by the Blessed One—who "
"knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha—practicing "
"which a diligent, keen, and resolute mendicant’s mind is freed, their "
"defilements are ended, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.353"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:15.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the householder Dasama said to Venerable Ānanda:"

#. VAR: sakideva → sakiṃdeva (s1, mr)
msgctxt "mn52:15.2"
msgid ""
"“seyyathāpi, bhante ānanda, puriso ekaṃva nidhimukhaṃ gavesanto sakideva "
"ekādasa nidhimukhāni adhigaccheyya;"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, suppose a person was looking for an entrance to a hidden treasure. And "
"all at once they’d come across eleven entrances!"

# reading savanaya
msgctxt "mn52:15.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ amatadvāraṃ gavesanto sakideva ekādasa "
"amatadvārāni alatthaṃ bhāvanāya."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I was searching for the door to the deathless. And all at "
"once I got to hear of eleven doors to the deathless."

msgctxt "mn52:15.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, purisassa agāraṃ ekādasadvāraṃ, so tasmiṃ agāre āditte "
"ekamekenapi dvārena sakkuṇeyya attānaṃ sotthiṃ kātuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person had a house with eleven doors. If the house caught fire "
"they’d be able to flee to safety through any one of those doors."

msgctxt "mn52:15.5"
msgid ""
"evameva kho ahaṃ, bhante, imesaṃ ekādasannaṃ amatadvārānaṃ ekamekenapi "
"amatadvārena sakkuṇissāmi attānaṃ sotthiṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I’m able to flee to safety through any one of these eleven "
"doors to the deathless."

msgctxt "mn52:15.6"
msgid ""
"Imehi nāma, bhante, aññatitthiyā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesissanti, "
"kimaṅgaṃ panāhaṃ āyasmato ānandassa pūjaṃ na karissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, those who follow other paths seek a fee for the teacher. Why shouldn’t "
"I make an offering to Venerable Ānanda?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn52:16.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro pāṭaliputtakañca vesālikañca "
"bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātetvā paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā "
"santappesi sampavāresi, "
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Dasama, having assembled the Saṅgha from Vesālī and "
